[
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "heading",
    "text": "Habakkuk 1"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "prose",
    "text": "This is the burden that Habakkuk the prophet received in a vision:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "How long, O LORD, must I call for help"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "but You do not hear,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "or cry out to You, “Violence!”"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "but You do not save?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Why do You make me see iniquity?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "Why do You tolerate wrongdoing?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Destruction and violence are before me."
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "Strife is ongoing, and conflict abounds."
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Therefore the law is paralyzed,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and justice never goes forth."
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "For the wicked hem in the righteous,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "so that justice is perverted."
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "“Look at the nations and observe—"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "be utterly astounded!"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "For I am doing a work in your days"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "that you would never believe"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "even if someone told you."
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "For behold, I am raising up the Chaldeans —"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "that ruthless and impetuous nation"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "which marches through the breadth of the earth"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "to seize dwellings not their own."
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "They are dreaded and feared;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "from themselves they derive justice and sovereignty."
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Their horses are swifter than leopards,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "fiercer than wolves of the night."
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Their horsemen charge ahead,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and their cavalry comes from afar."
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "They fly like a vulture,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "swooping down to devour."
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "All of them come bent on violence;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "their hordes advance like the east wind;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "they gather prisoners like sand."
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "They scoff at kings"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and make rulers an object of scorn."
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "They laugh at every fortress"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and build up siege ramps to seize it."
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Then they sweep by like the wind"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and pass on through."
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "They are guilty;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "their own strength is their god.”"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Are You not from everlasting,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "O LORD, my God, my Holy One?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "We will not die."
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "O LORD, You have appointed them"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "to execute judgment;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "O Rock, You have established them"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "for correction."
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Your eyes are too pure to look upon evil,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and You cannot tolerate wrongdoing."
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "So why do You tolerate the faithless?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "Why are You silent"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "while the wicked swallow up"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "those more righteous than themselves?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "You have made men like the fish of the sea,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "like creeping things that have no ruler."
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "The foe pulls all of them up with a hook;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "he catches them in his dragnet,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "and gathers them in his fishing net;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "so he rejoices gladly."
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Therefore he sacrifices to his dragnet"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and burns incense to his fishing net,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "for by these things his portion is sumptuous"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and his food is rich."
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Will he, therefore, empty his net"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and continue to slay nations without mercy?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "heading",
    "text": "Habakkuk 2"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "I will stand at my guard post"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and station myself on the ramparts."
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "I will watch to see what He will say to me,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and how I should answer when corrected."
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "prose",
    "text": "Then the LORD answered me:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "“Write down this vision"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and clearly inscribe it on tablets,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "so that a herald may run with it."
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "For the vision awaits an appointed time;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "it testifies of the end and does not lie."
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Though it lingers, wait for it,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "since it will surely come and will not delay."
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Look at the proud one; his soul is not upright —"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "but the righteous will live by faith —"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "and wealth indeed betrays him."
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "He is an arrogant man never at rest."
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "He enlarges his appetite like Sheol,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and like Death, he is never satisfied."
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "He gathers all the nations to himself"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and collects all the peoples as his own."
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Will not all of these take up a taunt against him,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "speaking with mockery and derision:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "‘Woe to him who amasses what is not his"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and makes himself rich with many loans!"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "How long will this go on?’"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Will not your creditors suddenly arise"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and those who disturb you awaken?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "Then you will become their prey."
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Because you have plundered many nations,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "the remnant of the people will plunder you—"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "because of your bloodshed against man"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and your violence against the land, the city,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and all their dwellers."
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Woe to him who builds his house"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "by unjust gain,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "to place his nest on high"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and escape the hand of disaster!"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "You have plotted shame for your house"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "by cutting off many peoples"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and forfeiting your life."
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "For the stones will cry out from the wall,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and the rafters will echo it from the woodwork."
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Woe to him who builds a city with bloodshed"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and establishes a town by iniquity!"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Is it not indeed from the LORD of Hosts"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "that the labor of the people only feeds the fire,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and the nations weary themselves in vain?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "For the earth will be filled"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "with the knowledge of the glory of the LORD"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "as the waters cover the sea."
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Woe to him who gives drink to his neighbors,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "pouring it from the wineskin until they are drunk,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "in order to gaze at their nakedness!"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "You will be filled with shame instead of glory."
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "You too must drink"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and expose your uncircumcision!"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "The cup in the LORD’s right hand"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "will come around to you,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and utter disgrace will cover your glory."
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "For your violence against Lebanon will overwhelm you,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and the destruction of animals will terrify you,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "because of your bloodshed against men"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and your violence against the land, the city,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and all their dwellers."
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "What use is an idol,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "that a craftsman should carve it—"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "or an image,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "a teacher of lies?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "For its maker trusts in his own creation;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "he makes idols that cannot speak."
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Woe to him who says to wood, ‘Awake!’"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "or to silent stone, ‘Arise!’"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "Can it give guidance?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Behold, it is overlaid with gold and silver,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "yet there is no breath in it at all.”"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "But the LORD is in His holy temple;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "let all the earth be silent before Him."
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "heading",
    "text": "Habakkuk 3"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "prose",
    "text": "This is a prayer of Habakkuk the prophet, according to Shigionoth:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "O LORD, I have heard the report of You;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "I stand in awe, O LORD, of Your deeds."
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Revive them in these years;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "make them known in these years."
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "In Your wrath, remember mercy!"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "God came from Teman,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and the Holy One from Mount Paran."
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Selah"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "His glory covered the heavens,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and His praise filled the earth."
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "His radiance was like the sunlight;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "rays flashed from His hand,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "where His power is hidden."
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Plague went before Him,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and fever followed in His steps."
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "He stood and measured the earth;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "He looked and startled the nations;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "the ancient mountains crumbled;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "the perpetual hills collapsed."
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "His ways are everlasting."
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "I saw the tents of Cushan in distress;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "the curtains of Midian were trembling."
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Were You angry at the rivers, O LORD?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "Was Your wrath against the streams?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Did You rage against the sea"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "when You rode on Your horses,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "on Your chariots of salvation?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "You brandished Your bow;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "You called for many arrows."
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Selah"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "You split the earth with rivers."
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "The mountains saw You and quaked;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "torrents of water swept by."
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "The deep roared with its voice"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and lifted its hands on high."
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Sun and moon stood still"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "in their places"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "at the flash of Your flying arrows,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "at the brightness of Your shining spear."
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "You marched across the earth with fury;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "You threshed the nations in wrath."
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "You went forth for the salvation of Your people,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "to save Your anointed."
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "You crushed the head of the house of the wicked"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and stripped him from head to toe."
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Selah"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "With his own spear You pierced his head,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "when his warriors stormed out to scatter us,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "gloating as though ready"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "to secretly devour the weak."
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "You trampled the sea with Your horses,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "churning the great waters."
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "I heard and trembled within;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "my lips quivered at the sound."
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Decay entered my bones;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "I trembled where I stood."
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Yet I must wait patiently for the day of distress"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "to come upon the people who invade us."
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Though the fig tree does not bud"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and no fruit is on the vines,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "though the olive crop fails"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and the fields produce no food,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "though the sheep are cut off from the fold"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and no cattle are in the stalls,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "yet I will exult in the LORD;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "I will rejoice in the God of my salvation!"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "GOD the Lord is my strength;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "He makes my feet like those of a deer;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Habakkuk",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "He makes me walk upon the heights!"
  }
]